article.description: Jack Lopez had a career-high 21 points as Montana had a strong second half to dominate Sacramento State 77-58 in Big Sky Conference action on Saturday night.
article.headline: Lopez leads Montana to 77-58 win over Sacramento State
article.linkText: Lopez leads Montana to 77-58 win over Sacramento State
article.story: MISSOULA, Mont. -- Jack Lopez had a career-high 21 points as Montana had a strong second half to dominate Sacramento State 77-58 in Big Sky Conference action on Saturday night. Lopez, who scored 15 in the second half, nailed 5 of 8 from beyond the arc and made 8 of 12 field goal attempts. Walter Wright made three from long range for 16 points and dished out a career-high 12 assists, and Martin Breunig added 15 points while grabbing 16 rebounds for Montana (9-6, 4-0), which has won five straight. The Grizzles never trailed and had a 37-28 lead at the break. They took command when Wright nailed a trey and Lopez followed with two straight 3-pointers to give Montana a 61-42 advantage with 11:53 remaining. Jeff Wu led the Hornets (7-7, 0-3) with 13 points. Justin Strings made 5 of 9 from the floor for 12.
